#28000
Lip of a Large Valley~
The huge walls of large, stony crags are broken here, allowing a small
road to snake down into what appears to be the mouth of a wide valley.
Stony, windswept crags jut into the air on either side of the trail,
shadowing the narrow defile that the trail leads through.  A massive gate
looms to the east, closing off access into the valley floor.  A few
clumps of dry, withered plantlife cling to the crevices and cracks that
run along the walls of the defile, their life protected from the blazing
sun by the shadow.
~
