#28001
Descending into the Valley~
The shadowed trail descends from the lip of the valley, fading in
places, distinct in others.  The crags press close from north and south,
their cracked, crumbling surface seemingly unscalable.  To the east, a
great wall seals the mouth of the valley beyond.  Squat and ugly, the
great stone wall is centered by huge wooden gates, and a number of
smaller ones, scattered along its half-mile length.
