Approaching the Holdfast Gate~
The trail emerges from it's narrow defile here, the stony crags leading
away to north and south to continue their circling of the valley.  A
broad, grassy field stretches from the foot of the crags to the base of
the towering wall, just to the east.  Visible on the wall, once one
approaches, are a large number of cracks and scorch marks, evidence of
violence.  Scraps of chitin and odd bits of broken bone litter the field,
some of the bones apparently humanoid.
